headline: MetLife (NYSE:MET) Reports Revenue Rise And Announces US$3 Billion Buyback Initiative
summary: MetLife (NYSE:MET) recently reported a robust earnings performance for Q1 2025, showing significant growth in both revenue and net income compared to the previous year. On the same date, the company announced a substantial share repurchase program, enhancing its capital management strategy. Over the past week, MetLife's share price saw a modest increase of 1.52%, aligning with broader market gains. The combination of positive earnings results and an active buyback program likely added...
